We booked 2 nights and extended one more night. We loved the hotel and staffs were very friendly. There were snacks, drink and can soups for free every night. The complimentory breakfast was in Chinese style, simple but pretty food. The hotel is a short walk from the main street. We arrived the city at the east station by high speed train. Shuttle bus line K1 is just outside the train station. We were told that taxi ride will be around 100 yuan, and only cost 10 yuan for K1 line. You can get off from Da Hongpao theater and walk 400 meter to the hotel. The hotel has umbrellas in the room for using anytime. The front desk will call taxi for you upon request, we took taxi to north train station, it costs us 60 yuan (about 8 dollar). Wuyishan is very pretty, we bought 3 days pass to the park, really enjoyed the visit. 
